<TEXT>
<P>
 If ... (Bravo Tuesday at 3 and 8 p.m.; Saturday at 6 and 11:30 p.m.) and O 
Lucky Man! (Bravo Tuesday at 5 p.m., Wednesday at 2 p.m., Saturday at 8 p.m.): 
Lindsay Anderson's dazzling, surreal 1969 study of rebellious boarding school 
students, and its 1973 sequel, which follows one of its students (Malcolm 
McDowell) into a rocky career as a coffee salesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The Last of the Mohicans (AMC Wednesday at 3 a.m.) is not as swiftly involving 
as the recent Daniel Day-Lewis remake of the James Fenimore Cooper novel set 
against the French and Indian War. But director Maurice Tourneur's 1920 version 
possesses the very quality the newest version lacks: pictorial grandeur. 
Barbara Bedford and Albert Roscoe star. 
</P>
