May 15, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Book Review; Page 10; Book Review Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
66 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FIBERARTS DESIGN BOOK FOUR edited by Nancy Orban (Lark Books: $21.95; 208 pp.) 
. This attractive volume is part of an ongoing survey of the work of artists 
and artisans from 24 countries. The most effective pieces remain true to 
traditional crafts and the nature of the material: weaving, tapestry, quilting. 
Many of the "art pieces" suggest unsuccessful copies of other media. 
</P>
