<P>
 BOHANNON'S COUNTRY by Joseph Hansen (Penguin: $5.95; 174 pp.). Set in the 
small coastal towns of central California, these neatly crafted mystery stories 
involve not Hansen's popular detective Dave Brandstetter, but ex-sheriff Hack 
Bohannon and his friends, a group of interesting, but never self-consciously 
"colorful" supporting characters.Hansen effectively depicts the kind of nasty 
little secrets that fester beneath the calm facades of small towns, especially 
in "Molly's Aim," in which a mildly retarded woman waits to take revenge on the 
high school hero who used her and discarded her. 
