<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AND ONE MORE THING: If Tom Petty's new single sounds awfully familiar, there's 
a reason. 
</P>
<P>
 The MCA release is "American Girl," one of the best-known tunes in Petty's 
rock repertoire for almost 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The song was included in Petty's 1976 debut album and released as a single at 
the time, but it failed to break into the Top 100. It was "Breakdown," a bluesy 
rocker from the same album, that subsequently introduced Petty to the pop 
charts. 
</P>
<P>
 MCA is turning now to "American Girl" -- which is part of Petty's recent 
greatest-hits album -- in hopes of following up the Top 10 success of "Mary 
Jane's Last Dance," according to Randy Miller, the company's senior vice 
president of marketing. "We think it's a timeless single. It sounds as good now 
as it did (in the '70s)."* 
</P>
</TEXT>
