<HEADLINE>
<P>
RWANDA GORILLAS BELIEVED UNHURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rwanda's rare mountain gorillas have remained unharmed despite a month of 
ethnic fighting in the Central African country, a conservationist said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no fighting in the forest of the Volcanoes National Park, which is 
home to the primates popularized in the Hollywood movie "Gorillas in the Mist," 
said Jose Kalpers, coordinator of the International Gorilla Conservation 
Program. 
</P>
<P>
 There remain about 600 mountain gorillas in the world, about half of which 
range through volcanoes straddling Rwanda, Uganda and Zaire. The other half 
live in a park farther north in Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
