<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP SWIMMING / SOUTHERN SECTION FINALS; ODELL LEADS LOYOLA TO TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ben Odell of Loyola won two individual events and helped on two relays to lead 
the Loyola boys' swim team to the Southern Section Division II championship 
Saturday at Belmont Plaza Pool. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola won with 217 points.Walnut won the girls' Division II team title with 
174 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Odell, a senior who plans to attend Harvard this fall, won the 200-yard 
freestyle in 1:40.09 and the 100-yard backstroke in 51.72. He also helped 
Loyola win the 200 medley relay in 1:36.63. 
</P>
<P>
 Odell, who had never won a Southern Section individual title, credited his 
friends in winning these. 
</P>
<P>
 "Look at that crowd," Odell said, pointing at the screaming Loyola fans. 
</P>
<P>
 John Jenkins, a Crescenta Valley senior, retained his titles in the 50 
freestyle in 20.62 and in the 100 freestyle in 45.88. He also anchored 
Crescenta Valley's 400 freestyle relay and 200 freestyle relay, which won in 
1:26.75, a Division II record time. 
</P>
<P>
 In girls' Division III, USC-bound Alexis Larsen led North Hollywood 
Harvard-Westlake to its first team title with 122 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Larsen retained her title in the 200 individual medley in 2:06, but failed to 
match the division record, 2:03.99, which she set last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Larsen also won her fourth-consecutive title in the 500 freestyle in 4:48.85, 
missing Stacy Shupe's record by .01. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridgecrest Burroughs won the boys' Division II title with 170 points. WENDY 
WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
