<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE BASEBALL PLAYOFF; IRVINE RALLIES TO DEFEAT CORONA DEL MAR, 6-5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ethan Gragnano came up with the two biggest hits of his varsity baseball 
career, sparking Irvine to a 6-5 come-from-behind victory in eight innings over 
Corona del Mar in a Sea View League playoff game Saturday at Tustin High. 
</P>
<P>
 Gragnano, the Vaqueros' No. 9 batter, hit a two-out single in the top of the 
eighth inning to score Eric Sonnenberg.Two innings earlier, Gragnano capped a 
four-run Vaquero rally with a two-out bloop single that scored Geoff Noisy and 
tied the score, 5-5, forcing extra innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine, which reached the Southern Section Division III finals the last two 
years, looked as though it would miss the playoffs this year after Corona del 
Mar took a 5-1 lead after three innings. Sea King shortstop Jeff Bowman had two 
hits and three runs batted in, and left-fielder Myles Davis had three hits and 
two runs scored. 
</P>
<P>
 But Irvine reliever Matt Ward, who replaced starter Eric Sobek in the third 
inning, shut out the Sea Kings for four innings, giving up three hits. GABE 
LACQUES 
</P>
</TEXT>
