<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; FULLERTON, IRVINE RUNNERS WIN AT BIG WEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton's Heather Killeen led a 1-2-3 county sweep Saturday in the women's 
5,000 meters at the Big West track and field championships in Las Cruces, N.M. 
</P>
<P>
 Killeen ran 17 minutes 51.10 seconds to edge Irvine's Laura Monson (17:51.47) 
and Traci Goodrich (18:10.28). 
</P>
<P>
 Monson, a freshman, came back to win the 3,000 in 10:17.85 with Killeen second 
in 10:28.73. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Michelle Merritt won the heptathlon with 4,558 points, overtaking 
Nevada's Janel Chandler in the final event. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine's David Mayeda, from University High, won the men's 400 hurdles with a 
career-best 51.09. Fullerton's Steve Frisone, was second in the 1,500 in 
3:52.28, and teammate Mike Tansley was third in the 5,000 in 15:02.40. 
</P>
<P>
 For the women, Irvine's Andrea Dean placed second in the 100 in 12.06 and 
third in the 200 in 25.06. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah State won the men's and women's team titles. The best county finish was 
by the Irvine women, who finished fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 CS Fullerton 11, USC 3 -- Mark Kotsay was four for four with two runs batted 
in, and Sal Mancuso was three for three with four RBIs for Fullerton (41-12). 
</P>
<P>
 Matt Wagner threw a seven-hitter, walking none and striking out six for his 
12th victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Walter Dawkins hit his 16th homer for the Trojans (34-18). 
</P>
<P>
 The teams conclude the series at 1 p.m. today at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 8-3, UC Santa Barbara 1-0 -- Trinity Johnson threw the 
second-game shutout, and Monica Bagalayos had four hits in two games for 
Fullerton, which finished the regular season 32-27, 21-11 in the Big West. 
</P>
</TEXT>
