<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; CANYONS LOSES LEAD, GAME, 8-5 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast College put together a pair of two-out rallies, scoring three 
runs in the fourth inning and four in the fifth, to defeat Canyons, 8-5, and 
oust the Cougars from the Southern California junior college softball regionals 
at Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons led, 5-4, entering the fifth, but April Crosby's two-run double broke 
a 5-5 tie and gave Orange Coast (31-14) the lead for good. 
</P>
<P>
 Danielle Bragdon had two hits and a run batted in, and Christina Schlender 
added an RBI double for Canyons (23-17), which defeated Orange Coast, 4-3, in a 
regional opener Friday. Freshman Marianne Winchester (12-5) took the loss, 
allowing 11 hits and six runs while striking out two. HIGH SCHOOL BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Avalon 12, Buckley 1 -- The Griffins lost their second game in as many days to 
host Avalon (12-0 in league play), which clinched the Liberty League title with 
the sweep of Buckley (15-5, 10-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Buckley was outscored by a combined 17-2 in the two games. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 7, Montclair Prep 6-Montclair Prep scored three runs in the seventh but 
stranded the tying run at second base in a nonleague loss. Andrew Miller had 
two hits, including his second home run of the season. Montclair Prep stranded 
12 runners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
