<HEADLINE>
<P>
HEIST FAILS; JAILED ROBBER SUES FOR LOOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who tried to rob a bank sued it from jail for $15 million, saying the 
bank had inflated its estimate of the amount of money it didn't lose. 
</P>
<P>
 Amil Dinsio, 58, who along with relatives tried to break into United Carolina 
Bank two years ago by hacking a hole in the roof, sued the bank in federal 
court, according to Friday's edition of The Charlotte Observer. 
</P>
<P>
 Speaking from jail in Loretto, Pa., Dinsio called the $15 million "just a 
figure," the paper said. "It's what you do in lawsuits. I'd be happy with a 
couple of million." 
</P>
</TEXT>
