<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLL FINDS ISRAELIS WOULD OBEY PALESTINIAN POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An opinion poll published Friday as Israeli troops turned over control of 
Jericho showed that a majority of Israelis would obey a Palestinian policeman's 
order to stop in self-rule areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dahaf Institute poll of 535 Israeli Jews, published in the Yedioth 
Ahronoth newspaper, showed 59% would obey an order to stop their cars in 
Palestinian self-rule areas, 30% said they would not and 11% did not respond. 
</P>
<P>
 Even among Jewish settlers in the occupied territories, many of whom oppose 
the Israel-PLO peace deal, more were ready to comply with Palestinian police 
commands than to disobey. Of 302 Jewish settlers polled, 45% said they would 
obey, 40% said they would not and 15% did not respond. 
</P>
