<TEXT>
<P>
 Nature Program--A free program on rain forest preservation will be presented 
at 10 a.m. Saturday at the Oak Canyon Nature Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is at 6700 Walnut Canyon Road in Anaheim.To reach it, take the 
Riverside Freeway east to Imperial Highway. Exit and head south to Nohl Ranch 
Road. Turn left and travel about three miles to Walnut Canyon Road, and turn 
left again. Go past the Anaheim Hills Golf Course; the nature center is at the 
end of the road, parking is on the left. 
</P>
<P>
 Call (714) 998-8380 for more information. 
</P>
<P>
 Bay Tours--A guided tour of the Upper Newport Bay Ecological Reserve will be 
offered at 9 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The tour is free and lasts about 2 1/2 hours. 
</P>
<P>
 Those who would like to participate are asked to meet at Shellmaker Island off 
Backbay Drive in Newport Beach. For more information, call (714) 640-6746. 
</P>
<P>
 Marsh Bird Walk--The Sea & Sage chapter of the National Audubon Society will 
hold a bird-watching walk at the San Joaquin Wildlife Sanctuary for both adults 
and 11- to 16-year-olds at 9:30 a.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The sanctuary is next to the chapter's Audubon House in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Advance reservations are not necessary. Beginning and advanced bird-watchers 
are welcome. Binoculars will be provided for the walk to participants who don't 
have their own. 
</P>
