<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: RESIDENTS INVITED TO PUBLIC WORKS WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks residents can get an up-close look at how city employees make 
signs, erase graffiti, sweep streets and maintain vehicles during National 
Public Works Week, beginning Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Municipal Service Center at 1993 Rancho Conejo Blvd. will host 
demonstrations and displays of public works equipment Monday through Thursday 
from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Landscape and tree maintenance crews will explain their duties and 
animal-control officers are scheduled to bring some furry pets to show 
visitors.Residents can also hop aboard a Thousand Oaks Transit bus for a ride 
through the city carwash, which uses recycled water. 
</P>
<P>
 To reserve a time for a group tour of the Municipal Service Center, call Sandi 
Bravo at 497-8611, Ext. 241. Individuals do not need to make reservations. 
STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
