<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE AT DWP CAUSES BLACKOUT IN VALLEY AREAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fire caused more than $2 million in damage to a Los Angeles Department of 
Water and Power receiving station late Friday and left 20,000 homes and 
businesses in the eastern San Fernando Valley without power for two hours, a 
DWP spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the blaze, which ignited in a transformer bank, is unknown, said 
Lucila Alvelais of the DWP. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire was reported just before midnight. Nine engine companies put the fire 
on Whitnall Highway out in 45 minutes, said Bob Collis of the Los Angeles City 
Fire Department. There were no injuries, and the cause of the fire is being 
investigated, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The power outage at the automated station affected portions of North 
Hollywood, Studio City, Burbank and Glendale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
