<P>
POKER GAME AT PARTY LEADS TO A SHOOTOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A friendly poker game erupted into a shootout Saturday in a rural area of 
Canyon Country, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 At about 7 p.m., three men playing cards during a party at a ranch in the 
16100 block of Sierra Highway got into an argument with their hosts over 
winnings and left the party.The men returned later and two of them got out of a 
car and fired an unknown number of shots at the house, said Sgt. Bruce 
Sonnenblick of the Santa Clarita Sheriff's Station.  
</P>
<P>
 Women and children were among about 25 guests at the party and were inside the 
house at the time of the shooting, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Martin Rico Hernandez, 30, of Canyon Country was arrested on 
suspicion of assault with a deadly weapon. 
</P>
<P>
 A .9-millimeter handgun and ammunition were found in his car, authorities 
said. The two shooters are still at large. 
</P>
