<HEADLINE>
<P>
KOOIMAN, STEWART REJOIN U.S. TO PLAY ARMENIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE CART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The U.S. national soccer team will make its final Orange County appearance 
before the World Cup when it plays host to the national team of Armenia today 
at 3:30 p.m. at Cal State Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Returning to the U.S. lineup are defender Cle Kooiman and striker Ernie 
Stewart. Kooiman, a central defender, has rejoined the team from Cruz Azul in 
the Mexican first division. Stewart played last season with Willem II in the 
Dutch first division. JULIE CART 
</P>
</TEXT>
