<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLUNTEERS NEEDED FOR TREE PLANTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking 50 or more volunteers to help plant 350 trees in Hollydale 
Park on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The tree-planting is scheduled for 9 a.m. to noon. Volunteers are asked to 
meet at the south entrance of the park near Century Boulevard, west of Garfield 
Boulevard. They are encouraged to wear hard-soled shoes, work gloves and hats, 
and bring shovels and sack lunches. Cold drinks will be provided. 
</P>
<P>
 The trees were provided in part through a $327,989 Department of 
Transportation grant that will fund 2,500 trees throughout the city during the 
next year. The total planting project will include $112,928 in city funds and 
about $88,000 in in-kind donations from the county, a city spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 750-0950. 
</P>
