<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH CENTRAL; GYM TO USE GRANT FOR BOXING GEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SANDRA HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Hoover Street Gym Foundation will use a $48,000 grant from the Amateur 
Athletic Foundation of Los Angeles to expand the gym at 7805 S. Hoover St., 
purchase boxing equipment and increase youth services. 
</P>
<P>
 The recent grant is part of a $1-million program set up by the Amateur 
Athletic Foundation following the 1992 riots to increase youth sports programs 
in areas affected by the violence. 
</P>
<P>
 The gym recently acquired a 10,000-square-foot facility on Washington 
Boulevard near Downtown. 
</P>
<P>
 "They showed us that their program wants to help youngsters and they will get 
our help," Barry Zepel, a spokesman for the Amateur Athletic Foundation, said 
of the gym. 
</P>
<P>
 "They are providing an outlet for youngsters to spend time in sports instead 
of something else." 
</P>
<P>
 The foundation was established with 40% of the profits from the 1984 Olympics. 
SANDRA HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
