<LENGTH>
<P>
87 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL; JORDAN COACH CAN'T TAKE 5TH IN 11-2 LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Apparently, Jordan Coach Ray Duron had seen enough. 
</P>
<P>
 After the Bulldogs gave up two runs on a lead-off walk and three consecutive 
singles, Duron pulled his team off the field in the bottom of the fifth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate won the Southeastern Conference game, 11-2. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was weird," said South Gate assistant coach Scott Pearson. "One minute we 
were playing and the next minute (Duron) pulled all his players." 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate catcher Danny Mojarro went three for three with one RBI and two 
runs scored. CHARLES SMITH 
</P>
