<TEXT>
<P>
 Marshall 3, Garfield 0 -- It took the minimum of three games for defending 
champion Marshall to eliminate the Bulldogs from a City 3-A semifinal at 
Marshall on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The scores were 15-1, 15-6, 15-7. 
</P>
<P>
 Art Sanchez led Garfield with only eight kills and seven blocks as the 
Barristers proved to be too powerful for the smaller Bulldogs. 
</P>
<P>
 Middle hitter Eli Brueggemann led Marshall with 15 kills, and hitter Jeff 
Grigsby had eight kills and six blocks. Setter Darry Tse had 38 assists and 
four aces for the Barristers. 
</P>
<P>
 It marked the last home game for Marshall Coach Marji Donatella, who will stay 
at the school but will pursue other interests. She was the boys coach for six 
seasons and led them to three consecutive City finals, winning the 3-A title 
last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield finished the season with a record of 13-4; the Barristers improved to 
16-0 and advanced to the finals for the third year in row. GARY CHAVEZ 
